    AKSA has never had an accident involving EDA that caused deaths, injuries, property or environmental damage, evacuations, or shelterings in place.
    An emergency action plan (Plant Emergency Procedure, C12-3-EMG01) has been established for the entire plant in accordance with the requirements of OSHA standard 1910.38 which addresses the following:
A?    escape procedure and routes; 
A?    procedure for post-evacuation employee accounting; 
A?    preferred means to report emergencies; 
A?    duties and procedures of employees who 1) remain to operate critical equipment and 2) perform rescue and medical duties; and
A?    The names for persons or locations to contact for more action plan information 
    The emergency action plan is reviewed with each affected employee when the plan is developed, the employee's responsibilities under the plan changes, whenever the plan is changed and upon initial hire.  Affected employees should assist in development of emergency plans for new facilities and be consulted for recommendations of existing plans.  The emergency action plan shall follow procedures for handling small releases.  A copy of the emergency action plan is included in Appendix VI of this document.
    AKSA has no planned changes for the EDA storage system.
